---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
import profileImage from '../assets/profile.jpeg';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={`About | ${SITE_TITLE}`} description="About Afsal Thaj" />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<section class="about-hero">
				<Image src={profileImage} alt="Afsal Thaj" class="about-photo" width={180} height={180} />
				<div>
					<h1>Afsal Thaj</h1>
					<p class="role">Senior Software Engineer · <a href="https://golem.cloud" target="_blank">Golem Cloud</a></p>
					<p class="stack">Durable Execution · Systems Engineering · Distributed Systems · Functional Programming</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="about-body">
				<p>
					I am a senior software engineer in Golem Cloud building an agent-native platform using Rust and WebAssembly — one that persists state,
					guarantees exactly-once external calls, provides full execution traces, and automatically recovers
					from crashes, outages, and network failures — <em>without relying on databases, queues, or schedulers.</em>
				</p>

				<p>
					Part of Golem almost from day one, I've made key contributions including building a
					<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TC6GXXUJ6jA" target="_blank">new programming language</a>
					to interact with Wasmtime and developing language-specific SDKs. All fully open source.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class="oss about-body" aria-label="Open-source key contributions">
				<h2>Open-source key contributions</h2>
				<ul class="oss-list">
					<li>
						<div class="oss-item-head">
							Author of
							<a href="https://github.com/zio/zio-config" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">zio-config</a>
						</div>
						<p class="oss-item-desc">
							Easily use and document any config from anywhere in ZIO apps — Scala, composable config layers, and
							multiple sources (e.g. HOCON).
						</p>
					</li>
					<li>
						<div class="oss-item-head">
							Author of
							<a href="https://github.com/zio/zio-constraintless" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">zio-constraintless</a>
						</div>
						<p class="oss-item-desc">
							A library for building DSLs where you can defer the existence of typeclass instances until
							interpretation.
						</p>
					</li>
					<li>
						<div class="oss-item-head">
							Active contributor to
							<a href="https://github.com/golemcloud/golem" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Golem</a>
							OSS
						</div>
						<p class="oss-item-desc">
							Open, Rust-based stack for durable distributed systems and WebAssembly: fault-tolerant workers,
							agents, and durable execution without you owning all the infrastructure.
						</p>
					</li>
					<li>
						<div class="oss-item-head">
							Author of
							<a href="https://github.com/afsalthaj/golem-timeline" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">golem-timeline</a>
						</div>
						<p class="oss-item-desc">
							Durable data engineering framework for timeline and analytics on Golem&rsquo;s durable
							execution.
						</p>
					</li>
					<li>
						<div class="oss-item-head">
							Author and maintainer of
							<a href="https://github.com/golemcloud/rib" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Rib</a>
						</div>
						<p class="oss-item-desc">
							A type-safe expression language to interact with WebAssembly components; powers scripting against
							Wasmtime in the Golem stack.
						</p>
					</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section class="timeline">
				<h2>Journey</h2>
				<div class="timeline-track">
					<div class="timeline-item">
						<span class="timeline-marker"></span>
						<div class="timeline-content">
							<span class="timeline-date">2023 — Present</span>
							<h3>Golem Cloud · USA</h3>
							<p>Building durable computing infrastructure with Rust & WebAssembly. Created Rib language, language SDKs, and <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9WjUBOfgriY" target="_blank">golem-timeline</a> — a data engineering layer powered by durable execution.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="timeline-item">
						<span class="timeline-marker"></span>
						<div class="timeline-content">
							<span class="timeline-date">2021 — 2023</span>
							<h3>Ziverge · USA</h3>
							<p>Built observability frameworks for a large streaming platform using Scala and Go. Deep work in the ZIO ecosystem — authored <strong>zio-config</strong>, my most notable contribution to the Scala ecosystem.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="timeline-item">
						<span class="timeline-marker"></span>
						<div class="timeline-content">
							<span class="timeline-date">Earlier career</span>
							<h3>Simple Machines, CBA & others · Sydney</h3>
							<p>Dozens of projects across half a dozen companies as a team lead, squad lead and developer. Gained deep experience in distributed computing, data engineering and ML ecosystems. Many of these projects made me fell in love with Functional Programming concepts too.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="timeline-item">
						<span class="timeline-marker"></span>
						<div class="timeline-content">
							<span class="timeline-date">Where it all began</span>
							<h3>Kochi · India</h3>
							<p>Where my engineering journey started. The roots that shaped everything that followed.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="about-cta">
				<div class="cta-cards">
					<a href="/talks" class="cta-card">
						<span class="cta-icon">▶</span>
						<span class="cta-label">Watch my talks</span>
					</a>
					<a href="https://github.com/afsalthaj" target="_blank" class="cta-card">
						<span class="cta-icon">⟨/⟩</span>
						<span class="cta-label">Open source work</span>
					</a>
					<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/afsal-thaj-10ab2842/" target="_blank" class="cta-card">
						<span class="cta-icon">in</span>
						<span class="cta-label">Connect on LinkedIn</span>
					</a>
				</div>
			</section>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	/* Hero */
	.about-hero {
		position: relative;
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 2em;
		padding: 3em 0 2em;
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
		margin-bottom: 2.5em;
		overflow: visible;
	}
	.about-hero::before {
		content: '';
		position: absolute;
		inset: -15% -10% -10%;
		pointer-events: none;
		background: radial-gradient(
			ellipse 90% 78% at 52% 28%,
			rgba(0, 255, 249, 0.028),
			transparent 70%
		);
		z-index: 0;
	}
	.about-hero > * {
		position: relative;
		z-index: 1;
	}
	.about-photo {
		width: 180px;
		height: 180px;
		border-radius: 50%;
		border: 2px solid var(--cyan);
		box-shadow:
			0 0 0 1px rgba(0, 255, 249, 0.35),
			var(--glow-cyan),
			0 0 28px rgba(0, 255, 249, 0.12);
		object-fit: cover;
		flex-shrink: 0;
	}

	@media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference) {
		.about-hero h1 {
			animation: about-hero-in 0.65s ease backwards;
		}
		.about-hero .role,
		.about-hero .stack {
			animation: about-hero-in 0.65s ease 0.08s backwards;
		}
		.about-photo {
			animation:
				about-hero-in 0.65s ease 0.18s backwards,
				about-photo-ring 3.2s ease-in-out 0.9s infinite;
		}
	}

	@keyframes about-hero-in {
		from {
			opacity: 0;
			transform: translateY(12px);
		}
		to {
			opacity: 1;
			transform: translateY(0);
		}
	}

	@keyframes about-photo-ring {
		0%,
		100% {
			box-shadow:
				0 0 0 1px rgba(0, 255, 249, 0.35),
				0 0 6px rgba(0, 255, 249, 0.34),
				0 0 14px rgba(0, 255, 249, 0.18),
				0 0 26px rgba(0, 255, 249, 0.08),
				0 0 28px rgba(0, 255, 249, 0.12);
		}
		50% {
			box-shadow:
				0 0 0 2px rgba(0, 255, 249, 0.45),
				0 0 10px rgba(0, 255, 249, 0.42),
				0 0 22px rgba(0, 255, 249, 0.22),
				0 0 34px rgba(0, 255, 249, 0.1),
				0 0 36px rgba(0, 255, 249, 0.16);
		}
	}
	.about-hero h1 {
		font-size: 2.4em;
		margin-bottom: 0.2em;
		text-shadow: var(--glow-cyan-hero);
	}
	.role {
		color: var(--text);
		font-size: 1em;
		margin: 0 0 0.3em;
	}
	.role a {
		color: var(--magenta);
	}
	.stack {
		color: var(--text-muted);
		font-size: 0.85em;
		margin: 0;
		letter-spacing: 0.03em;
	}

	/* Body */
	.about-body {
		max-width: 680px;
		margin-bottom: 3em;
	}
	.about-body p {
		color: var(--text);
	}
	.about-body em {
		color: var(--cyan);
		font-style: normal;
	}

	.oss h2 {
		font-size: 1.2em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.1em;
		margin: 0 0 1em;
	}
	.oss-list {
		list-style: none;
		padding: 0;
		margin: 0;
	}
	.oss-list li {
		color: var(--text);
		padding: 0.9em 0;
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
		line-height: 1.5;
	}
	.oss-list li:first-child {
		padding-top: 0;
	}
	.oss-list li:last-child {
		border-bottom: none;
		padding-bottom: 0;
	}
	.oss-item-head {
		color: var(--text);
		line-height: 1.45;
	}
	.oss-item-desc {
		margin: 0.4em 0 0;
		font-size: 0.88em;
		line-height: 1.6;
		color: var(--text-muted);
	}

	/* Timeline */
	.timeline {
		margin-bottom: 3em;
	}
	.timeline h2 {
		font-size: 1.2em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.1em;
		margin-bottom: 1.5em;
	}
	.timeline-track {
		position: relative;
		padding-left: 2em;
	}
	.timeline-track::before {
		content: '';
		position: absolute;
		left: 5px;
		top: 8px;
		bottom: 8px;
		width: 2px;
		background: linear-gradient(to bottom, var(--cyan), var(--magenta));
	}
	.timeline-item {
		position: relative;
		margin-bottom: 2em;
	}
	.timeline-item:last-child {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}
	.timeline-marker {
		position: absolute;
		left: -2em;
		top: 6px;
		width: 12px;
		height: 12px;
		border-radius: 50%;
		background: var(--bg);
		border: 2px solid var(--cyan);
		box-shadow: var(--glow-cyan);
	}
	.timeline-item:nth-child(2) .timeline-marker {
		border-color: var(--magenta);
		box-shadow: var(--glow-magenta);
	}
	.timeline-content {
		padding: 1em 1.2em;
		background: var(--bg-surface);
		border: 1px solid var(--border);
		border-radius: 6px;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
	}
	.timeline-content:hover {
		border-color: var(--cyan);
	}
	.timeline-date {
		font-family: 'Orbitron', sans-serif;
		font-size: 0.65em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.08em;
		color: var(--magenta);
	}
	.timeline-content h3 {
		font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
		font-size: 1.05em;
		color: var(--text);
		margin: 0.3em 0 0.4em;
	}
	.timeline-content p {
		font-size: 0.88em;
		color: var(--text-muted);
		margin: 0;
		line-height: 1.6;
	}
	.timeline-content a {
		color: var(--cyan);
	}

	/* CTA */
	.about-cta {
		margin-bottom: 2em;
	}
	.cta-cards {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
		gap: 1em;
	}
	.cta-card {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 0.6em;
		padding: 1.5em 1em;
		background: var(--bg-surface);
		border: 1px solid var(--border);
		border-radius: 6px;
		text-decoration: none;
		transition: all 0.25s ease;
	}
	.cta-card:hover {
		border-color: var(--cyan);
		box-shadow: var(--glow-cyan);
		transform: translateY(-2px);
	}
	.cta-icon {
		font-family: 'Orbitron', sans-serif;
		font-size: 1.4em;
		color: var(--magenta);
		transition: color 0.2s ease;
	}
	.cta-card:hover .cta-icon {
		color: var(--cyan);
		text-shadow: var(--glow-cyan);
	}
	.cta-label {
		font-family: 'Orbitron', sans-serif;
		font-size: 0.7em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.05em;
		color: var(--text-muted);
		text-align: center;
	}
	.cta-card:hover .cta-label {
		color: var(--text);
	}

	@media (max-width: 720px) {
		.about-hero {
			flex-direction: column;
			text-align: center;
		}
		.about-hero h1 {
			font-size: 1.8em;
		}
		.cta-cards {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}
</style>
